cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.LG 

This paper deals with evaluating the conformity of specific regulatory provisions to privacy norms, which involves aspects of cybersecurity (cs.CR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and machine learning (cs.LG) in the context of children's online privacy. The use of surveys to measure privacy expectations aligns with the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI), while the focus on IoT toy privacy norms suggests the sub-category of computer and society (cs.CY).
